description.narrative: UNICEF provided support to the government in ensuring continuity and quality of essential nutrition services during the COVID-19 pandemic. UNICEF successfully escorted the government to complete the in-service training on integrated management of acute malnutrition across all 34 provinces, and introduced mass screening protocol for child wasting across 10 provinces. UNICEF’s successful advocacy and technical support led to government’s policy decision to scale up our adolescent nutrition interventions nationwide through the National School Health Program as the delivery platform. | Status:Met | As-of Date:01/12/2020
